Through the pale door,
A hideous throng rush out forever,

—Edgar Allan Poe, "The Haunted Palace"

"Sometimes it is better to be swift of foot than strong of swordarm."
—Elven proverb

Her hand gently beckons, she whispers your name—
But those who go with her are never the same.

If any creatures with banding you control are blocking or being blocked by a creature, you divide that creature's combat damage, not its controller, among any of the creatures it's being blocked by or is blocking.)
